cfitsio
------------------------------------------
CFITSIO is a library of C and Fortran subroutines for reading and 
writing data files in FITS (Flexible Image Transport System) data 
format. CFITSIO provides simple high-level routines for reading and 
writing FITS files that insulate the programmer from the internal 
complexities of the FITS format. CFITSIO also provides many advanced 
features for manipulating and filtering the information in FITS files.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-51
  libgcc1-4.3.2-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-10
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.9-1
  gawk-3.1.6-2
  gcc4-core-4.3.2-2
  gcc4-fortran-4.3.2-2
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/docs/software/fitsio/fitsio.html

Canonical download:
  ftp://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/software/fitsio/c/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack cfitsio-3.140-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./cfitsio-3.140-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cfitsio-3.140-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/fpack-3.140-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libcfitsio-devel-3.140-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libcfitsio3-3.140-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

